Traineeship Description:

This position reports to the Head of Operations and together with our Account Managers, work with clients to deliver content for digital marketing.

Specific Responsibilities:

Trainee to be involved in:
1. Copywriting for website content
2. Content creation for social media such as Facebook and Instagram
3. Research and write articles on a variety of topics for digital publication

Competencies:

1. Content topic research and keywords seeding within content.
2. Research and create social media editorial calendar.
3. Produce digital content and adhere to strict timeline.
4. Create content that lead to business goals.
5. Learn SEO copywriting skillset to get content to appear on first page of Google.

Education Qualifications Required for this role: Degree

Eligibility Criteria for SGUnitedTraineeships:

• Singapore Citizen or Permanent Resident; and
a) Graduated or graduating in calendar year 2019 or 2020 from ITEs, polytechnics, universities, or other educational institutions (e.g. private universities and overseas institutions); or
b) Graduated earlier from above institutions and completed National Service in 2019 or 2020.